claim.claim-text:
A method of estimating a load bearing on a vehicle tire (12), the method comprising:
(A) deploying a deformation measuring sensor (16) in the vehicle tire (12), the deformation measuring sensor (16) generating a cyclical tire deformation signal indicative of tire deformation in a contact patch of a rolling tire;
(B) deploying a tire inflation pressure measuring sensor (22) in the vehicle tire (12), the inflation pressure measuring sensor measuring tire inflation pressure from within a tire cavity, and calculating a tire rolling speed estimation based upon the tire deformation signal;
(C) calculating a tire contact patch length estimation based upon the tire deformation signal;
(D) calculating a load estimation on the tire (12) based upon the tire inflation pressure, the tire contact patch length estimation, and the tire rolling speed estimation.

A system of estimating a load bearing on a vehicle tire, the system comprising:
(A) a vehicle tire (12) supporting a load;
(B) an inflation pressure measuring sensor (22) for measuring tire inflation pressure and generating a measured tire inflation pressure signal;
(C) a deformation measuring sensor (16) mounted in a tire region of the vehicle tire (12), the deformation measuring sensor (16) comprising a piezoelectric sensor for rotating with the tire region through a tire footprint thereby generating within the tire footprint a deformation signal indicative of opposite edge boundaries of a footprint contact patch and a length of the contact patch;
(D) a programmed data processor for calculating a contact patch length estimation from the deformation signal;
(E) a programmed data processor for calculating a tire rolling speed estimation from the deformation signal; and
(F)an artificial neural network programmed to adaptively interpret the tire rolling speed estimation, the contact patch length estimation, and the measured inflation pressure of the tire and generate an output load estimation based thereon.
